# 🛡️ EvilTwin Shield — Attack Detection & Awareness System

> **Educational cybersecurity tool** for simulating detection of Evil Twin (rogue Wi-Fi) attacks.  
> ⚠️ This project is strictly for educational and cybersecurity awareness purposes.

---

## 📸 Features

| Module | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| **Dashboard** | Live overview, threat stats, detection trend chart, attack vector radar |
| **Network Scanner** | 18 simulated Wi-Fi networks with risk scoring, signal meters, duplicate SSID detection |
| **Attack Awareness** | Evil Twin explained with flow diagram, 5-step walkthrough, IoC table |
| **Prevention & Safety** | 9 best-practice cards + interactive safety checklist |
| **Report Network** | Submit suspicious network reports with live community feed |
| **Admin Panel** | Threat logs, Networks DB, Feedback table, 3 analytics charts |

---

## 🗂️ Folder Structure

```
evil-twin-detector/
├── index.html              ← Complete standalone frontend (React-like SPA)
├── README.md
├── backend/
│   ├── server.js           ← Node.js + Express REST API + WebSocket
│   └── package.json
└── sample-data/
    └── networks.json       ← Sample Wi-Fi dataset (18 networks)
```

---

## 🚀 Quick Start

### Option A — Frontend Only (No Setup Required)
Just open `index.html` in any modern browser. All data is simulated in-browser.

---

### Option B — Full Stack (Frontend + Backend + MongoDB)

#### Prerequisites
- Node.js v18+
- MongoDB (local or MongoDB Atlas)

#### 1. Start the Backend

```bash
cd backend
npm install
# Local MongoDB:
node server.js

# With MongoDB Atlas:
MONGO_URI=mongodb+srv://user:pass@cluster.mongodb.net/eviltwin node server.js
```

Server starts on **http://localhost:3001**

#### 2. Open the Frontend

```bash
# Simply open index.html in your browser, OR serve it:
npx serve . -p 3000
```

Visit **http://localhost:3000**

---

## 📡 REST API Endpoints

| Method | Endpoint | Description |
|--------|----------|-------------|
| `GET` | `/api/health` | System health check |
| `GET` | `/api/networks` | All detected networks |
| `GET` | `/api/networks?risk=high` | Filter by risk level |
| `GET` | `/api/networks?dup=true` | Duplicate SSIDs only |
| `POST` | `/api/networks/scan` | Trigger a new scan |
| `GET` | `/api/networks/:bssid` | Get network by BSSID |
| `GET` | `/api/logs` | All threat logs |
| `PATCH` | `/api/logs/:id/status` | Update log status |
| `GET` | `/api/feedback` | All user reports |
| `POST` | `/api/feedback` | Submit new report |
| `GET` | `/api/analytics/summary` | Dashboard stats |
| `GET` | `/api/analytics/trends` | 7-day trend data |

